#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn36.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Sagāthāvagga "
msgstr "1. With Verses "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn36.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Sallasutta "
msgstr "6. An Arrow "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.208, sc1
#. VAR: vedayati → vediyati (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.1"
msgid "“Assutavā, bhikkhave, puthujjano sukhampi vedanaṃ vedayati, dukkhampi vedanaṃ vedayati, adukkhamasukhampi vedanaṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, an uneducated ordinary person feels pleasant, painful, and neutral feelings. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.2"
msgid "Sutavā, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sukhampi vedanaṃ vedayati, dukkhampi vedanaṃ vedayati, adukkhamasukhampi vedanaṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "An educated noble disciple also feels pleasant, painful, and neutral feelings. "

#. VAR: adhippayāso → adhippāyo (bj, mr) | adhippāyaso (s1-3, km) | adhippāyoso (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.3"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, ko viseso ko adhippayāso kiṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanenā”ti? "
msgstr "What, then, is the difference between an ordinary uneducated person and an educated noble disciple?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.4"
msgid "Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe … "
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.5"
msgid "assutavā, bhikkhave, puthujjano dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "“When an uneducated ordinary person experiences painful physical feelings they sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.6"
msgid "So dve vedanā vedayati—"
msgstr "They experience two feelings: "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.7"
msgid "kāyikañca, cetasikañca. "
msgstr "physical and mental. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: sallena vijjheyya → sallena vijjheyyuṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.8"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, purisaṃ sallena vijjheyya. "
msgstr "It’s like a person who is struck with an arrow, "

#. VAR: sallena anuvedhaṃ vijjheyya → sallena anuvedhaṃ vijjheyyuṃ (bj, s1-3, km) | sallena vijjheyyuṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.9"
msgid "Tamenaṃ dutiyena sallena anuvedhaṃ vijjheyya. "
msgstr "only to be struck with a second arrow. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.10"
msgid "Evañhi so, bhikkhave, puriso dvisallena vedanaṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "That person experiences the feeling of two arrows. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.11"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno socati kilamati paridevati urattāḷiṃ kandati sammohaṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "In the same way, when an uneducated ordinary person experiences painful physical feelings they sorrow and pine and lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.12"
msgid "So dve vedanā vedayati—"
msgstr "They experience two feelings: "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.13"
msgid "kāyikañca, cetasikañca. "
msgstr "physical and mental. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.14"
msgid "Tassāyeva kho pana dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno paṭighavā hoti. "
msgstr "When they’re touched by painful feeling, they resist it. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.15"
msgid "Tamenaṃ dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighavantaṃ, yo dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo, so anuseti. "
msgstr "The underlying tendency for repulsion towards painful feeling underlies that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.16"
msgid "So dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno kāmasukhaṃ abhinandati. "
msgstr "When touched by painful feeling they look forward to enjoying sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.17"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.18"
msgid "Na hi so, bhikkhave, pajānāti assutavā puthujjano aññatra kāmasukhā dukkhāya vedanāya nissaraṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Because an uneducated ordinary person doesn’t understand any escape from painful feeling apart from sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.19"
msgid "tassa kāmasukhañca abhinandato, yo sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo, so anuseti. "
msgstr "Since they look forward to enjoying sensual pleasures, the underlying tendency to greed for pleasant feeling underlies that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.20"
msgid "So tāsaṃ vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti. "
msgstr "They don’t truly understand feelings’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.21"
msgid "Tassa tāsaṃ vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ appajānato, yo adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo, so anuseti. "
msgstr "The underlying tendency to ignorance about neutral feeling underlies that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.22"
msgid "So sukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, saññutto naṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "If they feel a pleasant feeling, they feel it attached. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.23"
msgid "Dukkhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, saññutto naṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "If they feel a painful feeling, they feel it attached. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:1.24"
msgid "Adukkhamasukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, saññutto naṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "If they feel a neutral feeling, they feel it attached. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:1.25"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘assutavā puthujjano saññutto jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, saññutto dukkhasmā’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "They’re called an uneducated ordinary person who is attached to rebirth, old age, and death, to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn36.6:2.1"
msgid "Sutavā ca kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno na socati, na kilamati, na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na sammohaṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "When an educated noble disciple experiences painful physical feelings they don’t sorrow or pine or lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:2.2"
msgid "So ekaṃ vedanaṃ vedayati—"
msgstr "They experience one feeling: "

msgctxt "sn36.6:2.3"
msgid "kāyikaṃ, na cetasikaṃ. "
msgstr "physical, not mental. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.210, sc3
msgctxt "sn36.6:3.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, purisaṃ sallena vijjheyya. "
msgstr "It’s like a person who is struck with an arrow, "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ dutiyena sallena anuvedhaṃ na vijjheyya. "
msgstr "but was not struck with a second arrow. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.3"
msgid "Evañhi so, bhikkhave, puriso ekasallena vedanaṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "That person would experience the feeling of one arrow. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:3.4"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno na socati, na kilamati, na paridevati, na urattāḷiṃ kandati, na sammohaṃ āpajjati. "
msgstr "In the same way, when an educated noble disciple experiences painful physical feelings they don’t sorrow or pine or lament, beating their breast and falling into confusion. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.5"
msgid "So ekaṃ vedanaṃ vedayati—"
msgstr "They experience one feeling: "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.6"
msgid "kāyikaṃ, na cetasikaṃ. "
msgstr "physical, not mental. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:3.7"
msgid "Tassāyeva kho pana dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno paṭighavā na hoti. "
msgstr "When they’re touched by painful feeling, they don’t resist it. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.8"
msgid "Tamenaṃ dukkhāya vedanāya appaṭighavantaṃ, yo dukkhāya vedanāya paṭighānusayo, so nānuseti. "
msgstr "There’s no underlying tendency for repulsion towards painful feeling underlying that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:3.9"
msgid "So dukkhāya vedanāya phuṭṭho samāno kāmasukhaṃ nābhinandati. "
msgstr "When touched by painful feeling they don’t look forward to enjoying sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.10"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.11"
msgid "Pajānāti hi so, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako aññatra kāmasukhā dukkhāya vedanāya nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "Because an educated noble disciple understands an escape from painful feeling apart from sensual pleasures. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.12"
msgid "Tassa kāmasukhaṃ nābhinandato yo sukhāya vedanāya rāgānusayo, so nānuseti. "
msgstr "Since they don’t look forward to enjoying sensual pleasures, there’s no underlying tendency to greed for pleasant feeling underlying that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:3.13"
msgid "So tāsaṃ vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavaṃ ca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "They truly understand feelings’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.14"
msgid "Tassa tāsaṃ vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānato, yo adukkhamasukhāya vedanāya avijjānusayo, so nānuseti. "
msgstr "There’s no underlying tendency to ignorance about neutral feeling underlying that. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:3.15"
msgid "So sukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaññutto naṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "If they feel a pleasant feeling, they feel it detached. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.16"
msgid "Dukkhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaññutto naṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "If they feel a painful feeling, they feel it detached. "

msgctxt "sn36.6:3.17"
msgid "Adukkhamasukhañce vedanaṃ vedayati, visaññutto naṃ vedayati. "
msgstr "If they feel a neutral feeling, they feel it detached. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:3.18"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘sutavā ariyasāvako visaññutto jātiyā jarāya maraṇena sokehi paridevehi dukkhehi domanassehi upāyāsehi, visaññutto dukkhasmā’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "They’re called an educated noble disciple who is detached from rebirth, old age, and death, from sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress, I say. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.6:3.19"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, viseso, ayaṃ adhippayāso, idaṃ nānākaraṇaṃ sutavato ariyasāvakassa assutavatā puthujjanenāti. "
msgstr "This is the difference between an educated noble disciple and an uneducated ordinary person. "

# NOTE: Text seems to require an implicit “mental” (supplied by BB and Thanissaro) or an idiomatic sense of vedayati as “affected” (Woodward). I follow the latter.
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn36.6:4.1"
msgid "Na vedanaṃ vedayati sapañño, "
msgstr "A wise and learned person isn’t affected "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:4.2"
msgid "Sukhampi dukkhampi bahussutopi; "
msgstr "by feelings of pleasure and pain. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:4.3"
msgid "Ayañca dhīrassa puthujjanena, "
msgstr "This is the great difference in skill "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Mahā → ayaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn36.6:4.4"
msgid "Mahā viseso kusalassa hoti. "
msgstr "between the wise and the ordinary. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn36.6:5.1"
msgid "Saṅkhātadhammassa bahussutassa, "
msgstr "A learned person who has comprehended the teaching "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Vipassato → sampassato (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn36.6:5.2"
msgid "Vipassato lokamimaṃ parañca; "
msgstr "discerns this world and the next. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:5.3"
msgid "Iṭṭhassa dhammā na mathenti cittaṃ, "
msgstr "Desirable things don’t disturb their mind, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:5.4"
msgid "Aniṭṭhato no paṭighātameti. "
msgstr "nor are they repelled by the undesirable. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn36.6:6.1"
msgid "Tassānurodhā athavā virodhā, "
msgstr "Both favoring and opposing "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:6.2"
msgid "Vidhūpitā atthagatā na santi; "
msgstr "are cleared and ended, they are no more. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:6.3"
msgid "Padañca ñatvā virajaṃ asokaṃ, "
msgstr "Knowing the stainless, sorrowless state, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn36.6:6.4"
msgid "Sammā pajānāti bhavassa pāragū”ti. "
msgstr "they understand rightly, going beyond rebirth.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.6:6.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
